<item>
            <title>[FLINK-2156] Scala modules cannot create logging file</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-2156</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The Scala only modules &lt;tt&gt;flink-scala-shell&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;flink-ml&lt;/tt&gt; use Maven&apos;s scalatest plugin to run their tests. The scalatest plugin has no &lt;tt&gt;forkNumber&lt;/tt&gt;, though. Therefore, the logging fails to create the logging file as specified in the &lt;tt&gt;log4j-travis.properties&lt;/tt&gt; file.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We can fix this issue by giving these two modules different &lt;tt&gt;log4j.properties&lt;/tt&gt; files which don&apos;t require a &lt;tt&gt;forkNumber&lt;/tt&gt;. Or we fix the &lt;tt&gt;forkNumber&lt;/tt&gt; to 1.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
