                            <comment id="14947402" author="githubbot" created="Wed, 7 Oct 2015 19:13:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Github user StephanEwen commented on the pull request:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/1234#issuecomment-146299251&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/1234#issuecomment-146299251&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    We do execute multiple tests concurrently (multiple forks). Does this lead to problems when all forks see the fork number &quot;1&quot; ? I am wondering, because at some places, we use the fork number to prevent port conflicts.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    Then again, how could these parts have worked before when the fork number was missing in the first place?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
